dcterms:description: The Penn Treebank (PTB) is a large annotated corpus of English, which includes a wide variety of texts and is used for training and evaluating natural language processing models.
dcterms:title: Penn Treebank (PTB)

dcterms:description: The Universal Dependency 2.0 English branch (UD-English) is a dataset used for training and evaluating models on part of speech tagging and dependency parsing tasks.
dcterms:title: Universal Dependency 2.0 English branch (UD-English)

dcterms:description: The CoNLL 2017 shared task development and test data is used for evaluating models on dependency parsing tasks, providing a benchmark for performance comparison.
dcterms:title: CoNLL 2017 shared task development and test data
